### WEEK 6: Multi-Tool Workflows — AI Power Combos

*Theme: Combining multiple AI tools for exponentially more powerful results.*

---

#### Day 36: Text + Image — Visual Creation

📖 **Concept:** AI isn't just text. Image generation (Midjourney, DALL-E in ChatGPT, Stable Diffusion) lets you create visuals for anything: marketing materials, social media posts, presentations, product mockups, art, and more. The key workflow: use text AI to write the image prompt, then use image AI to generate it.

🌍 **Real Story:** A food truck owner in Austin used ChatGPT to write descriptions of her menu items, then used DALL-E to create stylized images of each dish for her Instagram. Before: 50 followers. After 3 months: 4,200 followers and a line around the block.

🔨 **Exercise (20 min):**
1. Open ChatGPT (DALL-E is built in) or try [Canva AI](https://canva.com)
2. Prompt: *"Create an image of [something you actually need — a logo concept, a social media graphic, an illustration for a presentation, or just something beautiful]."*
3. Iterate on the image: *"Make it more [colorful/minimalist/professional/warm]. Change the [element] to [new idea]."*
4. Try the text-to-image-prompt workflow:
   - First: *"Write a detailed image generation prompt for [what you want]. Include style, mood, colors, composition, and details."*
   - Then: Use that prompt with an image generator

👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 **Family Bonus:** Let everyone generate their "dream room" or "fantasy world." Kids LOVE this. Create album covers for imaginary bands. Design your family's dream house.

🔗 **Resource:** [Midjourney](https://midjourney.com) — $10/mo, best quality. Or use DALL-E in ChatGPT (free tier available).

💭 **Reflection:** *What visual content have you always wanted to create but couldn't because you "can't draw"? What if that barrier just disappeared?*

---

#### Day 37: Text + Voice — Audio Content

📖 **Concept:** AI can generate natural-sounding speech in dozens of voices and languages. Combined with text AI, you can create podcasts, audiobooks, voiceovers, language learning tools, and accessibility content. ElevenLabs and others offer remarkably human-sounding voices. You can even clone your own voice (ethically, with consent).

🌍 **Real Story:** A blind entrepreneur in Nigeria creates an audio newsletter for his community using AI text generation + AI voice synthesis. He "writes" by speaking to ChatGPT, edits the transcript, then converts to audio. 500 subscribers who wouldn't read an email now listen every week.

🔨 **Exercise (20 min):**
1. Write something using AI (a summary, a story, an announcement)
2. Go to [ElevenLabs](https://elevenlabs.io) (free tier available)
3. Paste your text. Choose a voice. Generate audio.
4. Listen. This is how you create:
   - Audio versions of written content (accessibility!)
   - Podcasts from AI-generated scripts
   - Voice memos from text notes
   - Bedtime stories in different character voices

👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 **Family Bonus:** Create a personalized bedtime story with AI, then generate it in audio with character voices. Kids will want this EVERY night.

🔗 **Resource:** [ElevenLabs](https://elevenlabs.io) — Free tier, multiple voices and languages.

💭 **Reflection:** *How many people in the world can't read but can listen? What does AI voice mean for accessibility?*

---

#### Day 38: Text + Code — Building Without Coding

📖 **Concept:** You don't need to be a programmer to build things with AI. ChatGPT, Claude, and others can write code for you — websites, calculators, data tools, automations, apps. You describe what you want in plain English, and AI writes the code. This isn't about becoming a programmer. It's about removing a barrier that used to require a $100K developer.

🌍 **Real Story:** A teacher in Kentucky asked ChatGPT to build a simple grade calculator web page. No coding experience. In 20 minutes, she had a working tool that her students used all semester. When it broke, she told the AI what was wrong, and it fixed it.

🔨 **Exercise (20 min):**
1. Think of a simple tool you wish existed
2. Prompt: *"I want to build a simple [web page/calculator/form/tool] that [what it does]. I don't know how to code. Give me the complete code with instructions on how to run it. Make it simple and explain each step."*
3. Try it! ChatGPT's code interpreter can even run code for you directly.
4. Ideas: a tip calculator, a workout tracker, a recipe scaler, a budget tracker, a quiz for your kids

👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 **Family Bonus:** Build a simple website together — a family page, a pet page, a hobby page. Kids learn that code isn't magic; it's instructions.

🔗 **Resource:** [Replit](https://replit.com) — Free, run code in your browser with AI assistance.

💭 **Reflection:** *What tool or app have you wished existed? What if you could build it yourself in an afternoon?*

---

#### Day 39: Workflow Automation — Connecting AI to Your Apps

📖 **Concept:** The real magic happens when AI connects to the apps you already use. Zapier, Make, and IFTTT let you create automated workflows: "When I get an email from [person], summarize it and send me a Slack message." "When I add a row to my spreadsheet, generate a report." No coding required.

🌍 **Real Story:** A solopreneur running an Etsy shop connected Zapier to her store: when a new order arrives, AI automatically generates a personalized thank-you message, creates a shipping label, and updates her inventory spreadsheet. She went from 2 hours/day on admin to 15 minutes.

🔨 **Exercise (20 min):**
1. Go to [Zapier](https://zapier.com) (free tier: 100 tasks/month)
2. Create an account and explore the templates
3. Build your first "Zap" — start simple:
   - "When I get an email, save it to a Google Sheet"
   - "When I add a calendar event, send me a reminder message"
   - "When I save an article to Pocket, summarize it with AI"
4. Or just explore what's possible: Browse Zapier's AI-powered templates

👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 **Family Bonus:** Automate a family task — automatic grocery list generation, shared calendar reminders, or weekly family newsletter compilation.

🔗 **Resource:** [Zapier](https://zapier.com) for simplicity, [Make](https://make.com) for more complex workflows.

💭 **Reflection:** *What repetitive task do you do every week that a robot should be doing instead?*

---

#### Day 40: Multi-Modal Projects — Combining Everything

📖 **Concept:** Today you put it all together. The most powerful AI users don't use one tool — they chain them. A typical power user workflow: research with Perplexity → draft with Claude → generate images with Midjourney → create a presentation with Canva AI → add voiceover with ElevenLabs → automate distribution with Zapier. Each tool does what it does best. You're the conductor.

🌍 **Real Story:** A church volunteer in Alabama created an entire community outreach campaign in one weekend: AI-researched local needs → AI-drafted messaging → AI-generated flyers → AI-voiced robocalls for elderly members → automated email distribution. Work that used to take a team of 5 was done by one person with an internet connection.

🔨 **Exercise (25 min):**
Create a complete multi-tool project. Choose one:

**Option A — Business Launch Kit:** Research your market (Perplexity) → Write your pitch (Claude) → Design your logo/mockups (DALL-E/Canva) → Create your one-page website (ChatGPT code)

**Option B — Content Package:** Research a topic (Perplexity) → Write an article (Claude) → Generate illustrations (Midjourney/DALL-E) → Convert to audio (ElevenLabs) → Create social media posts (Canva AI)

**Option C — Teaching Package:** Design a lesson plan (Claude) → Create visual aids (DALL-E) → Build a quiz (ChatGPT code) → Generate audio instructions (ElevenLabs) → Create handouts (Canva AI)

👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 **Family Bonus:** Create a family project together — a family cookbook with AI recipes and AI-generated illustrations, a family history with AI-enhanced old photos, or a neighborhood guide.

🔗 **Resource:** [AI Jason on YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/@AIJason) — Multi-tool workflow tutorials.

💭 **Reflection:** *Look at what you just built. A year ago, this would have required a designer, a writer, a developer, and a producer. You did it in 25 minutes.*

