#### Day 53: AI for Global Impact

📖 **Concept:** AI's most profound impact may not be in wealthy nations with high-speed internet. It may be in developing countries where a single AI-powered device can replace systems that never existed: doctors in areas with no hospitals, teachers in areas with no schools, financial advisors in areas with no banks. When Genesis says "a billion people with a digital partner in their corner," the billion who need it most aren't in Silicon Valley.

🌍 **Real Story:** In Bangladesh, BRAC — one of the world's largest NGOs — is deploying AI chatbots to provide real-time health guidance to community healthcare workers serving 130 million people. Workers in remote villages can ask about symptoms, drug interactions, and nutrition protocols. For many patients, this is the most "medical expertise" they've ever had access to.

