#### Day 110: The Invention That Matters — Your Moonshot

📖 **Concept:** Everyone has at least one idea that could change the world. Most people dismiss it as impossible, impractical, or "not for someone like me." AI dissolves those barriers. With AI, you can research the feasibility of any idea, prototype it, test it, refine it, and start building it — in weeks, not years. Today, you're going to design your moonshot.

🔨 **Exercise (30 min):**
This is the biggest exercise in the curriculum. Take it seriously.

1. The Problem: *"What is the ONE problem in the world that I care most about? The thing that keeps me up at night, that breaks my heart, that I would fix if I had unlimited power?"*

2. The Vision: *"Describe a world where this problem is solved. What does that look like? How are people's lives different? Paint the picture in vivid detail."*

3. The AI Invention: *"Now help me design an AI-powered solution to this problem. Don't limit yourself to what exists today. Think 3-5 years out. What would I build? How would it work? Who would it help? What's the 'emergent intelligence' — the way the system gets smarter as more people use it?"*

4. The First Step: *"What's the smallest possible version of this I could build or start THIS MONTH? Not the whole vision. Just the first step. Make it concrete."*

5. Write it down. Save it. This is your moonshot document. Come back to it.

💡 **Imagination Spark:** Scott's moonshot was Genesis — a platform where every human on Earth has a digital partner in their corner. What's yours? It doesn't have to be a company. It could be a movement, a tool, a community, a piece of art, a discovery. What's the thing that only YOU could create, because only YOU have your specific combination of experiences, passion, and skills?

👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 **Family Bonus:** Each family member designs their moonshot. Even young kids. ESPECIALLY young kids. A child who learns to think in moonshots becomes an adult who creates them.

🔗 **Resource:** [XPRIZE](https://www.xprize.org/) — See how moonshot challenges drive breakthrough innovation.

💭 **Reflection:** *"The best way to predict the future is to create it." What future are you going to create?*

